
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `enchant-2` baraye baresi dorosti neveshtari (spell checking) va pishnahad kalamehaye dorost estefade mishavad. In dastoor jozi az ketabkhaneye Enchant ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `enchant-2 -l`  --> 📚 List kardan zabanhaaye dastras baraye spell checking.
    🔹 `enchant-2 -d <zaban>`  --> 🔍  Entkhab farhang zaban moshakhas baraye spell checking (masalan, `enchant-2 -d en_US` baraye zabaneh English Amricaai).
    🔹 `enchant-2 -a`  --> ✍️  Namayesh pishnahadha baraye kalamehaye eshtebah.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ echo "in matn ashtebah darad" | enchant-2

    🔹 Baresi matn az vorudi va chap kardan natijeh dar khoruji.

    $ enchant-2 -l

    🔹 Namayesh list zabanhaaye poshtibani shodeh.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ echo "yek nemat az rahe ashtebah" | enchant-2 -a -d en_US

    🔹 Spell check va namayesh pishnahadha baraye kalamehaye eshtebah dar matn dadeh shodeh ba estefadeh az farhangzabaneh American English.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `enchant-2` command is used for spell checking and suggesting corrections. It's part of the Enchant library.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `enchant-2 -l`  --> 📚 List available languages for spell checking.
    🔹 `enchant-2 -d <language>`  --> 🔍  Select a specific language dictionary for spell checking (e.g., `enchant-2 -d en_US` for American English).
    🔹 `enchant-2 -a`  --> ✍️  Display suggestions for misspelled words.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ echo "this text has miistakes" | enchant-2

    🔹 Checks the text from input and prints the result to output.

    $ enchant-2 -l

    🔹 Displays the list of supported languages.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ echo "a blesssing in the skies" | enchant-2 -a -d en_US

    🔹 Spell checks and displays suggestions for misspelled words in the given text using the American English dictionary.
